---
---
<section id="about" class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-10 py-32">
  <span class="section-label fade-up">// About</span>
  
  <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.5rem,6vw,3.5rem)] font-black leading-none mb-20 fade-up">
    Developer.<br />
    Designer.<br />
    Builder.
  </h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-24">
    <!-- Left — Bio -->
    <div class="space-y-8 font-mono text-[10px] text-paper-dim leading-[1.9] fade-up">
      <p>
        I'm a frontend developer and UI/UX designer working across frameworks, 
        mapping tools, and design systems. I've been shipping real things 
        on the web for years — before AI tools existed, and sharper 
        because of them now.
      </p>
      <p>
        From political simulators to wiki bots to live event platforms — 
        I own projects end to end, from concept and Figma to deployed code.
      </p>
      <p>
        Design sensibility and technical depth in the same person. I build with 
        modern tools and AI-assisted workflows to move fast without losing what's under the hood.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Right — Stats Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-white/5 border border-white/5 fade-up">
      {[
        { val: '5+', label: 'Projects shipped' },
        { val: '3+', label: 'Years building' },
        { val: '6+', label: 'Frameworks used' },
        { val: '∞', label: 'Tabs open' },
      ].map((stat) => (
        <div class="bg-ink-surface p-8 flex flex-col justify-center items-center text-center">
          <span class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-paper mb-2">{stat.val}</span>
          <span class="font-mono text-[8.5px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-paper-ghost">{stat.label}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
